[src:container-registry/spec-api-p02] Create, update, delete and retrieve manifests.
[src:container-registry/spec-api-p02] Fetch the manifest identified by `name` and `reference` where `reference` can be a tag or digest.
[src:container-registry/spec-api-p02] A `HEAD` request can also be issued to this endpoint to obtain resource information without receiving all data.
[src:container-registry/spec-api-p02] The manifest identified by `name` and `reference`.
[src:container-registry/spec-api-p02] The contents can be used to identify and resolve resources required to run the specified image.
[src:container-registry/spec-api-p02] Put the manifest identified by `name` and `reference` where `reference` can be a tag or digest.
[src:container-registry/spec-api-p02] The manifest has been accepted by the registry and is stored under the specified `name` and `tag`.
[src:container-registry/spec-api-p02] The received manifest was invalid in some way, as described by the error codes.
[src:container-registry/spec-api-p02] One or more layers may be missing during a manifest upload.
[src:container-registry/spec-api-p02] If so, the missing layers will be enumerated in the error response.
[src:container-registry/spec-api-p02] Delete the manifest or tag identified by `name` and `reference` where `reference` can be a tag or digest.
[src:container-registry/spec-api-p02] Note that a manifest can *only* be deleted by digest.
[src:container-registry/spec-api-p02] The specified `name` or `reference` were invalid and the delete was unable to proceed.
