[src:container-registry/spec-api-p02] Clients can assume the manifest or tag was already deleted if this response is returned.
[src:container-registry/spec-api-p02] Manifest or tag delete is not allowed because the registry is configured as a pull-through cache or `delete` has been disabled.
[src:container-registry/spec-api-p02] Operations on blobs identified by `name` and `digest`.
[src:container-registry/spec-api-p02] Used to fetch or delete layers by digest.
[src:container-registry/spec-api-p02] Retrieve the blob from the registry identified by `digest`.
[src:container-registry/spec-api-p02] The blob identified by `digest` is available.
[src:container-registry/spec-api-p02] The blob content will be present in the body of the request.
[src:container-registry/spec-api-p02] The blob identified by `digest` is available at the provided location.
[src:container-registry/spec-api-p02] There was a problem with the request that needs to be addressed by the client, such as an invalid `name` or `tag`.
