[src:container-registry/spec-api-p02] This can happen when the range is not formatted correctly or if the range is outside of the valid size of the content.
[src:container-registry/spec-api-p03] This endpoint can be used to create resumable uploads or monolithic uploads.
[src:container-registry/spec-api-p03] If successful, an upload location will be provided to complete the upload.
[src:container-registry/spec-api-p03] Optionally, if the `digest` parameter is present, the request body will be used to complete the upload in a single request.
[src:container-registry/spec-api-p03] Upload a blob identified by the `digest` parameter in single request.
[src:container-registry/spec-api-p03] This upload will not be resumable unless a recoverable error is returned.
[src:container-registry/spec-api-p03] The blob has been created in the registry and is available at the provided location.
[src:container-registry/spec-api-p03] Initiate a resumable blob upload with an empty request body.
[src:container-registry/spec-api-p03] The `Location` header must be used to complete the upload.
[src:container-registry/spec-api-p03] The response should be identical to a `GET` request on the contents of the returned `Location` header.
[src:container-registry/spec-api-p03] Mount a blob identified by the `mount` parameter from another repository.
[src:container-registry/spec-api-p03] The blob has been mounted in the repository and is available at the provided location.
[src:container-registry/spec-api-p03] Clients should never assemble URLs for this endpoint and should only take it through the `Location` header on related API requests.
[src:container-registry/spec-api-p03] The `Location` header and its parameters should be preserved by clients, using the latest value returned via upload related API calls.
[src:container-registry/spec-api-p03] Retrieve status of upload identified by `uuid`.
[src:container-registry/spec-api-p03] The primary purpose of this endpoint is to resolve the current status of a resumable upload.
[src:container-registry/spec-api-p03] Retrieve the progress of the current upload, as reported by the `Range` header.
[src:container-registry/spec-api-p03] The last received offset is available in the `Range` header.
[src:container-registry/spec-api-p03] There was an error processing the upload and it must be restarted.
[src:container-registry/spec-api-p03] Upload a chunk of data for the specified upload.
[src:container-registry/spec-api-p03] Upload a stream of data to upload without completing the upload.
[src:container-registry/spec-api-p03] The stream of data has been accepted and the current progress is available in the range header.
[src:container-registry/spec-api-p03] The updated upload location is available in the `Location` header.
